**[1863, 02-16] Ms.A.1.2.32.10A**

Gerrit Smith to WLG

“You close your letter with: ‘Remember England.’ But today’s news of the
Great Emancipation Meetings in England makes me feel that she can get
along very well without my help. If any American Abolitionist visits
England it must, I think be you.” He is willing to “contribute a hundred
dollars” to such a tour.


